The '''Angola slaty flycatcher''' ('''''Melaenornis brunneus''''') is a small [[passerine]] [[bird]] in the [[Old World flycatcher|flycatcher]] family [[Muscicapidae]]. It is sometimes placed in the [[genus]] ''[[Dioptrornis]]'' instead of ''Melaenornis''. As suggested by its [[common name]], it is [[Endemism|endemic]] to [[Angola]].

